images
======

Visual assets referenced from the README and the per-example
walkthroughs. Generated by ParaView or the frontend's 3D viewer
and committed as PNG.

Required files (the docs reference these — they should exist before
the public release):

  - header-strip.png        4 thumbnails side-by-side, ~900×220 px,
                              shown at the top of the README. Order:
                              u-shape, z-bend, inner-outer, cylindrical.
  - u-shape.png             U-shape pipe velocity field, ~700 px wide.
  - z-bend.png              Z-bend temperature + velocity.
  - inner-outer-pipe.png    Inner/outer pipe temperature field.
  - cylindrical-cht.png     Cylindrical CHT temperature field
                              (the LN2 regasifier shot — counter-flow
                              gradient).

Recommended export settings:

  - PNG, transparent background where possible.
  - 2× device-pixel-ratio for HiDPI displays.
  - Compressed via pngquant or oxipng before committing
    (keeps the repo small).

Diagrams (architecture, etc.) live alongside as .svg so they
stay legible at any zoom.
